LAGOS – Transport Minister, Rotimi Amechi only fears in his bid to get the All Progressive Congress nomination is the presence of Prof. Yemi Osinbajo, the sitting Vice President in the race. His campaign sources revealed this weekend that the notion that Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu is the APC front runner should be discarded, saying he fears is the presence of Osinbajo in the race. The source reveals that Amechi’s confidence is premised on his relationship with the northern oligarchy which a function of the facilities he sited in that region as transport Minister. “Amechi is confident of getting the north delegates behind him, but for Osinbajo,” the source said at the weekend. “And the reason is because of Osinbajo’s presence in the presidency. You can’t will that fact away. The presidency wills slot of influence and he’s is key player there.” The source was emphatic that Tinubu’s chances of securing the APC ticket is very remote and will likely pitch his camp with another political party.